  <tr>
	<td bgcolor="#707070" align="left">
		<font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" color="#FFFFFF" size="1">
		<STRONG>Guild Forming on Tunare</STRONG> []
		·· 02-03-2000 at 11:12 AM ·· ^<a href="#top">top</a></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td bgcolor="#202050">
	    <font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" size="-2"><br>
		[We received this announcement via email]<p><EM><br>To be located on the Tunare server, this all-female guild<br>(tentatively called She-of-Shadows) will be dedicated to fostering a<br>sense of sisterhood among the dark races of Norrath, providing us with<br>the opportunity to advance our characters in an environment that would<br>otherwise be unavailable to us. True, there are other all female<br>guilds on the Tunare server, but it can be difficult for evil<br>classes/races to gain admittance into them. And while the evil guilds<br>undoubtedly allow female characters, none are made specifically for<br>women. And so, She-of-Shadows was born. <p>The requirements for joining the guild are few:<p>- Your character must be female. The guild concept was concieved with<br>women gamers in mind, but males who play a female character are<br>welcome.<p>- Your character must be of a dark alignment: dark elves, trolls, and<br>ogres are the races this guild is geared toward, but shadow knights<br>and necromancers of 'light' races will also be accepted.<p>- Both PvP  and -PvP characters are welcome.<p>- Evil roleplaying is definately not discouraged as long as you stay<br>within the guidelines set forth by Verant's 'Play Nice' policy. In<br>other words, you can still roleplay evil without having to kill steal,<br>if your PvP switch is on (or you are in a PvP area) do not corpse<br>camp, etc.<p>If you are interested, feel free email me at <A HREF="mailto:venus_envy@postmark.net">venus_envy@postmark.net</A> [clickable] or send a /tell to Djalai in-game. More information on the guild can be found at: <A HREF="http://sheofshadows.cjb.net">http://sheofshadows.cjb.net</A> [clickable].<br></EM>
		<p><font size="1">
		<STRONG>- <a href="mailto:keeper@neriak.com">The Keeper</a></STRONG></font></font></td>
  </tr>
</table><p>
